begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 For 
\begin_inset Formula $U\subseteq X$
\end_inset

 open consider the map 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathcal{F}(U)\longrightarrow\prod_{x\in U}\mathcal{F}_{x},\qquad s\mapsto(s_{x})_{x\in U}.
\]

\end_inset

We claim that this map is injective if 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

 is a sheaf.
 Indeed, let 
\begin_inset Formula $s,t\in\mathcal{F}(U)$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{x}=t_{x}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in U$
\end_inset

.
