\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{example}
\backslash
label{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{O}_{X}$
\end_inset

 be the sheaf of holomorphic functions on an open subset 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

.
 For every open subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $U\subseteq X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in\mathcal{O}_{X}(U)$
\end_inset

, we let 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{U}(f):=f'$
\end_inset

 be the derivative.
 We obtain a morphism 
\begin_inset Formula $D:\mathcal{O}_{X}\to\mathcal{O}_{X}$
\end_inset

 of sheaves of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

-vector spaces.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

 is surjective because locally every holomorphic function has a primitive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

But there exist open subsets 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and functions 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 on 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 that have no primitive.
 For instance 
\begin_inset Formula $U=B_{r}(z_{0})\backslash\{z_{0}\}$
\end_inset

 contained in 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $f:z\mapsto1/(z-z_{0})$
\end_inset

.
 More precisely, by complex analysis we know that 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{U}$
\end_inset

 is surjective if and only if every connected component of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 is simply connected.
 The sufficiency of this condition will also be an immediate application
 of cohomologial methods developed later.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

We obtain an exact sequence of sheaves of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

-vector spaces 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{center}
\backslash
begin{tikzcd} 0 
\backslash
arrow[r] & 
\backslash
mathbb{C}_X 
\backslash
arrow[r, "
\backslash
iota "]  & 
\backslash
mathcal{O}_X 
\backslash
arrow[r, "D"]  & 
\backslash
mathcal{O}_X 
\backslash
arrow[r]  & 0 
\backslash
